{"type": "article", "id": 38675, "title": "树叶启发太多设计，其实它自己也是好设计的一部分｜这个设计了不起", "description": "每个周末，《好奇心日报》都会找个主题为你寻找精彩设计。", "date": "2017-03-11T00:34:02Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 18824, "name": "ilsangisang"}, {"id": 38427, "name": "leaf republic"}, {"id": 38428, "name": "T3DESIGN"}, {"id": 38429, "name": "Susanna Bauer"}, {"id": 38430, "name": "前田麦"}, {"id": 38431, "name": "Tang Chiew Ling"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 9, "praise_count": 351, "image": "img/article/article_show/201703110834339vwMRqkUNxLFW2nc.jpg", "contents": "<p>        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #323333} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p5 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p6 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #323333; min-height: 25.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} span.s2 {font-kerning: none; color: #323333} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><p class=\"\">作为观察季节变化的最佳参照物，多彩且随手可得的树叶是不少设计师和艺术家的素材库——在处理得当的情况下，你会发现它们并没有想象中那么脆弱。</p><h3>leaf republic</h3><p>为了减少一次性塑料产品带来的污染，德国初创公司 <a href=\"http://www.leaf-republic.com/\">leaf republic</a> 以树叶为原材料，研发了一批可以真正做到自然分解的餐盘。为了保证餐盘足够坚韧且不会漏水，设计团队采用了 2+1 复合结构：盘子的第一和第三层都是利用棕榈叶纤维缝合而成的大张树叶，中间则是用树叶纤维制成的纸。当它们上机台热压成型后，就成了只需 28 天就能回归自然循环的环保餐盘。你可以通过<a href=\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/s?merchant=A8BVX3ODAIOQ1&amp;fallThrough=3\">链接</a>购买到旗下的产品，售价从 8.59 英镑起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234558dpgTjJv0Lq3CQWaO.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.553125\" data-format=\"gif\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234557i7nA5ITVtFex8UvN.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563235\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703102345576YgazpIhO9K2T0iw.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.567647\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234557JBUwtzIMX6kNT3yW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563235\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>SOULeaf by ilsangisang</h3><p>来自韩国的 <a href=\"http://ilsangisang.com/\">ilsangisang</a> 是一间擅于从自然界的动植物中汲取灵感的设计工作室。在这套名为 SOULeaf 的灯饰系列中，设计师用经过认证的环保型纸张重现了银杏、悬铃木和榆树的树叶，它们分别来自首尔街头以及巴黎和纽约的公园。为了尽可能地还原树叶的细节，叶脉也通过丝网印刷的方式印在了灯罩外，所使用的夜光油墨让这些灯饰能够在不同的明暗环境下呈现出三种独特的风格。除了 3D 版之外，每一款灯饰还配有一张平面的印刷品作为装饰。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234620hF3gTEBwuXpKnYWy.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.733496\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234619SfKzUxPY7M80QuNA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.524450\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234620dQYB946bWrJsOc3S.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.733496\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234620YwOkRgqu2y7EUxJ8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.733496\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234620TYVmGAyZrt5iE7uS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.733496\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234620gpLKoxRN7zPTS9cM.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.733496\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Leaf Thermometer by 熊谷英之</h3><p>借鉴树叶随季节变化而变色的特性，日本设计公司 <a href=\"http://www.t3design.co.jp/\">T3DESIGN</a> 的熊谷英之带来了这款叶子形状的<a href=\"http://www.t3design.co.jp/?business=%E3%83%97%E3%83%AD%E3%83%80%E3%82%AF%E3%83%88%E3%83%87%E3%82%B6%E3%82%A4%E3%83%B3%E3%80%80%E3%83%AA%E3%83%BC%E3%83%95\">温感便签纸</a>。在 20 到 25 摄氏度的环境下，叶子会呈现出绿色，低于或是高出这一温度范围时，就会变成入冬后的棕褐色或是入秋后的金黄色。和常见的温度计相比，以这种模拟自然的方式感知温度显然要有趣得多。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/NIHON-ICHIBAN-D-710-S-Leaf-Thermometer/dp/B00A6LI3GG\">购买链接</a>，售价为 10.55 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234638mZ4L315qAhalCHJD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234637I1QbMwN5f6ryxD9R.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.663366\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234638GloRETASF9gaijU4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Leaves 2D &amp; 3D by Susanna Bauer</h3><p>在德国艺术家 <a href=\"http://www.susannabauer.com/\">Susanna Bauer</a> 的手下，枯黄的落叶摆脱了脆弱不堪的形象，反而变成了一张张有着独特纹路的“布料”：有些被缝上了漂亮的镶边，有些则化为像是用皮革制成的立方体雕塑。在 Bauer 看来，在枯叶上穿针引线和人与人之间的相处颇为类似，充满了微妙和紧张感，最终将会趋于脆弱与坚韧之间的平衡。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703102346590YW56LHGfQcqhDtj.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.661667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234659rauqdleLFHRfDwK0.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234659g1NPXf3sK7thYHA6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234659UC5IaXSdATnDe23V.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.680000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234700yIcFwZNXnkJL4sb9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703102346597UrgX1wPiuLhycCs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Leaf Beast by 前田麦</h3><p>有了落叶的加持，凶悍的野兽在这套名为 Leaf Beast 系列雕塑中变得毫无杀伤力可言，看起来像是幻想世界中性格温顺的小动物。为了帮助它们“成功转型”，日本艺术家<a href=\"http://bakumaeda.tumblr.com/\">前田麦</a>仅在收集来的木兰花叶上做最基本的轮廓雕刻，并不进行额外的加工。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234715IZSE7FQRxVTUtKdJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.662451\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234716P4mBQxaY7yjRFgrq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.662451\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234715YS8bV3FhgyvmL4ad.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.662451\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310234716JGPB1kauXnh5sUim.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.662451\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703102347169xEX7y0BeiRZm6hT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.662451\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Fashion in Leaf by Tang Chiew Ling</h3><p>用树叶做成的服饰不稀奇，那么礼服设计稿呢？来自马来西亚的 <a href=\"http://www.behance.net/tangchiewling\">Tang Chiew Ling</a> 是一名擅长用树叶讲故事的平面设计师，这套名为 Fashion in Leaf 的“迷你礼服”就是她用母亲花园里的叶子拼成的，叶梗的部分刚好构成了肩带，相当讨巧。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310235018SeLYsh1xK0iO67j9.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.712899\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310235018TUDwRu5jvQl80ZeN.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.424411\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703102350184wnAfaz8ei6rgFQB.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.371706\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310235019bnk3VwYCxvGytdlg.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.426667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310235019PGRsot65X4UVTbzW.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.447989\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170310235019h5vwtDVBepCYon9y.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.460472\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}